<h1><a id="top">Psychology of Religion</a></h1>

<h2>Religiosity and Suicide</h2>
<p><a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0131715">Religion and Completed Suicide: a Meta-Analysis</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Religion overall plays a protective role in preventing suicide amongst its adherents</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://academic.oup.com/aje/article/155/5/413/171404">Suicide Rates and Religious Commitment in Young Adult Males in Utah</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Higher levels of religiosity are inversely correlated with suicide</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7310534/#:~:text=Several%20studies%20have%20found%20lower,after%20adjusting%20for%20social%20support">Religion and Suicide Risk: a systematic review</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Religion appears to reduce suicide attempts and completed suicides but not suicidal ideation</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>This may be due to religion providing access to a supportive community, shaping a person&rsquo;s beliefs about suicide, providing a source of hope and providing ways to interpret suffering</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>However this relationship is complex</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>Religiosity and Mental Health</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/10508619.2020.1729570">Does Spirituality or Religion Positively Affect Mental Health? Meta-analysis of Longitudinal Studies</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Finds a small but positive effect of spirituality or religion on mental health</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fmed.2022.877213/full">Religiosity/Spirituality and Mental Health in Older Adults: A Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis of Observational Studies</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>High levels of religiosity and spirituality is associated with lower depressive symptoms and less anxiety</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/364086091_A_Meta-Analysis_of_ReligionSpirituality_and_Life_Satisfaction">A Meta-Analysis of Religion/Spirituality and Life Satisfaction</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Religion and spirituality is significantly and positively associated with life satisfaction</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Further Information:</p>
<p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8462234/">Spirituality, religiousness, and mental health: A review of the current scientific evidence</a></p>
<p><a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/1468-5906.t01-1-00160">Religiosity and Mental Health: A Meta&ndash;Analysis of Recent Studies</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fpsyt.2023.1097598/full">A meta-analytic review of the associations between dimensions of religious coping and psychological symptoms during the first wave of the COVID-19 pandemic</a></p>
<h2>Religiosity and Sense of Purpose</h2>
<p><a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/jopy.12401">When God is your only friend: Religious beliefs compensate for purpose in life in the socially disconnected</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>For socially connected individuals, a religious belief in itself has minimal impact on their sense of purpose in life</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>However, for those who are socially disconnected, being highly religious predicted greater levels of purpose in life</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4580713/">The Role of Meaning in Life Within the Relations of Religious Coping and Psychological Well-Being</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meaning in life is a crucial element of religious coping and psychological well-being</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/009164718601400105">The Association between Religiosity and the Purpose-in-Life Test: Does it Reflect Purpose or Satisfaction?</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Conservative religiosity is associated with high levels of a sense of purpose in life</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Further Information:</p>
<p><a href="https://news.gallup.com/poll/113575/complex-relationship-between-religion-purpose.aspx">The Complex Relationship Between Religion and Purpose</a></p>
<h2>Religiosity and Crime</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0191886996000232">Crime and religion: An international comparison among thirteen industrial nations</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Looks at 13 industrial countries over the period of 1990-1991</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>More religious countries had lower crime rates, at least in terms of property crimes</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/0022427801038001001#:~:text=The%20results%20of%20the%20meta,effect%20on%20individuals'%20criminal%20behavior">&ldquo;If You Love Me, Keep My Commandments&rdquo;: A Meta-Analysis of the Effect of Religion on Crime</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Finds that religion has a moderate deterrent effect on crime</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://scholarlycommons.obu.edu/articles/131/">Religion, Delinquency, and Drug Use: A Meta-Analysis</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Meta-analysis</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Religion is negatively association with involvement in delinquent behaviors</p>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>Further Information:</p>
<p><a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/315651531_Religion_and_Crime_A_Systematic_Review_and_Assessment_of_Next_Steps">Religion and Crime: A Systematic Review and Assessment of Next Steps</a></p>

